parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the BCM can cause various electrical systems to malfunction, including the airbag system, anti-lock braking system (ABS), and interior lighting, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

The failure of the clutch hydraulic system can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
and inability to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the HVAC blower motor resistor can cause the blower motor to malfunction, leading to overheating, electrical fires, and loss of heating and air conditioning.
symptoms: Blower motor only works on high speed

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Vehicle stalls or will not start

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake light switch can cause the brake lights to malfunction, leading to accidents or injuries.

The rust and corrosion of the frame can cause the vehicle to become unsafe to drive, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. The failure of the frame can also lead to loss of control, rollover, or separation of the bed from the cab.
symptoms: separation of the bed from the cab
and excessive shaking or vibration while driving.
